Thank you very much for trying out **<span style="color: #d52f30;">Mer</span><span style="color: #d5d5d5;">kop</span><span style="color: #ffd31e;">ian</span> Democracy**

> *"Such a general development cannot be attributed to the false tactics of any single party or to the mistakes of individual leaders. On the contrary, the conduct of individual leaders is determined largely by the sentiments of the people as a whole. It would be erroneous, however, to regard the sentiments of the moment as reflecting the natural make-up and character of the people. They are merely the consequence of the special circumstances which have brought about this profound degradation of the entire nation."*

 - Karl Kautsky, *Hitlerism and Social Democracy*, 1934

This is a game of alternate history, a <span style="color: #d52f30;">Mer</span><span style="color: #d5d5d5;">kop</span><span style="color: #ffd31e;">ian</span> History.  

For more information on the politics and government of the Merkopian Federation, see the "Library" page on the top left. If this is your first time playing the game, it is strongly recommended that you read at least some of this information. 

- @1928_easy: Begin (easy difficulty) *Sunshine and lollipops*
- @1928_main: Begin (normal difficulty) *Prefered Way to play the game*
- @1928_historical: Begin (historical mode) *Hard Mode*

@1928_easy
on-arrival: difficulty = -2; resources = 5; dues = 5; z_relation = 45; dvp_relation = 40; budget = 5; fvp_modifer = 1.1; ldp_modifer = 1.1; gdsu_modifer = 1.1;
go-to: 1928_main

@1928_historical
subtitle: Saving, loading, and polls will be disabled. [? if not achievement_game_completed: Not recommended for a first playthrough. ?]
on-arrival: {!
Q.difficulty = 2;
Q.historical_mode = 1;
Q.resources = 3;
Q.dues = 2;
Q.reformist_dissent = 25;
Q.agrarnians_dissent = 25;
Q.revolutionaries_dissent = 35;
